Reasoning: The paper discusses the interconnection theory for electrical circuits that switch and oscillate as interconnections of passive components with operational amplifiers (op-amps). This topic falls under the domain of Electrical Engineering and Control Systems, which are covered by several arXiv CS sub-categories. cs.ET (Embedded Systems) is the most likely category as it deals with the design and analysis of electronic circuits. cs.SY (Systems and Control) is also a likely category as it covers the analysis and control of dynamical systems, which includes electrical circuits. cs.CE (Computational Engineering, Finance, and Science) covers the use of computational methods in engineering, which could include the analysis of circuits. cs.EM (Electromagnetism) covers the study of electromagnetic fields and their interactions with matter, which is relevant to the analysis of circuits. Finally, cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) covers the use of neural networks and evolutionary algorithms in engineering, which could be applied to the design of circuits.
